content: It's a good game, but nothing special compared to the 10 other Kairosoft games like it. We want something new, not Food Shop over and over again. Game is way to RNG heavy, contest seem almost random sometimes, even if stats are 100% on my side I still lost twice. Several small things that are really annoying, but 3 of 5 overall. Not too great but not bad either. But too expensive! 5$ for a recycled game? Hell no!

I've been a fan of Kairosoft games since Game Dev Story, and have bought almost every single game after that. So it pains me to realize that all their games, for some reason, perform INCREDIBLY sluggish and laggy on my phone. I'm currently using an LG G3 running android 6, and almost every game runs very slow and studdery. The phone itself is very powerful, so there is no reason why these games should be underperforming. I would advise everyone interested in Kairosoft titles to err to the side of caution.
It's a great concept but I'm extremely confused how I could lose a challenge when I was the best in both categories, popularity and charisma.

A fun game WITHOUT COMMERCIALS  That said, these are its two major flaws:  1. Lack of in-game guidance or online resources for understanding the game  2. The creator, Kairosoft, apparently does not yet understand the value of creating updates for their apps. They could honestly release the tiniest updates ever for their games and it would be a much appreciated sign of good faith to their customers.

Kairosoft does release a lot of these food games but this one is really head and shoulders above the rest. I thought this was pretty good from the start, and then I unlocked the ability to make my own noodles and soups. That really put it over the top. Honestly though I kinda hate doing facility building stuff (never did like Hot Spring Story or World Cruise Story, for example) but the rest of the game is so good I don't even care. Contests! Put your ingredients where you want! Total customization!

I couldn't put it down, colorful, addictive simulation game. It needs lots more special items and opportunities to unlock bonuses and special equipment. I reached year 11 and now what? Having just come from Game Dev Story, I can easily say this tops it with no hesitation. Along with having a familiar feel that all Kairosoft games have, this game expands upon the already extremely solid game play that this caliber of games is known for by adding a plethora of mechanics and factors into the game play while not feeling like too much. This with the cutesy aesthetics of the Kairosoft games really makes this an overall gem in the Play Store. Highly recommended.

Out of all if the Kairosoft games, this one is the most complex. If you're a veteran of their games, it's a lot of fun, but if you're new to this style of game, I would suggest trying out another Kairosoft game first.

People who say that this is the same as the rest obviously didn't play long. Not only can you design your own dishes as in Bon Bon Cakery, and design a store like in sushi spinnery, you can make noodles and broth from scratch and design your dishes from the ground up. New bells and whistles add more events and design possibilities while one works to muscle out competitors who try to cut into your profits. I really recommend this Kairosoft title.
